SIMPLE: swordfish
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Swordfish
<hw>Sword"fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A very large oceanic fish
(<spn>Xiphias gladius</spn>), the only representative of the family
<fam>Xiphiidae</fam>. It is highly valued as a food fish. The bones of
the upper jaw are consolidated, and form a long, rigid, swordlike beak;
the dorsal fin is high and without distinct spines; the ventral fins are
absent. The adult is destitute of teeth. It becomes sixteen feet or more
long.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The gar pike.</def> <sd>(c)</sd> <def>The
cutlass fish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A southern constellation. See
<er>Dorado</er>, 1.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Swordfish sucker</b></col> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>, <cd>a
remora (<spn>Remora brachyptera</spn>) which attaches itself to the
swordfish.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Swordick</ent>⟦br⟧
